{"title_page": "Mercedes-Benz Zetros", "text_new": "The '''Mercedes-Benz Zetros''' is an off-road truck for extreme operations. It was first presented at the 2008 [[Eurosatory]] defence industry trade show in Paris. The Zetros is manufactured at the [[Mercedes-Benz]] plant in [[W\u00f6rth am Rhein|W\u00f6rth]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cms.daimler.com/Projects/c2c/channel/documents/1828804_Daimler_Trucks_at_a_Glance_2012_en.pdf |title=Daimler Trucks at a Glance |year=2012 |page=25 |publisher=Daimler |accessdate=25 April 2012 }}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The truck is designed to be compatible with the [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|Hercules C-130]] transport and also fits into a standard German railway carriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.special-trucks.eu/webspecial_zetros/ |title=Transportable |work=The New Zetros |publisher=Mercedes Benz |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz Zetros DSC01477.JPG|thumb|Zetros 2733 at the [[International Defence Industry Exhibition]] 2012]]\n\n== Variants ==\nThe Zetros is available with a choice of 326&nbsp;hp (240&nbsp;kW) or 428&nbsp;hp (315&nbsp;kW) engines<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com/en/trucks/zetros/powertrain|title=Powertrain|website=ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref> and all-wheel drive:\n* Zetros 1833 (4x4) \u2013 4,000 to 6,000&nbsp;kg payload\n* Zetros 2733 (6x6) \u2013 7,000 to 10,000&nbsp;kg payload\n\nAlthough normally used as a truck, the Zetros has also been put to work as an off-road tractor unit in the middle east.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mercedes' Middle Eastern Monster Mover\u2014the Zetros 6x6 gets down to work on Biglorryblog!|url=http://www.commercialmotor.com/big-lorry-blog/mercedes-middle-eastern-monster-mover--the-zetros-6x6-gets-down-to-work-on-biglorryblog#.UMvGNW9yGE0|work=Biglorryblog|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> German company Harald Bruhn also introduced a Zetros-based agricultural trailer truck as the Secutor.<ref>[https://www.truckanddriver.co.uk/latest-stories/don-t-say-zetros-say-secutor-the-latest-mercedes-agricultural-monster-mover-on-biglorryblog/ Don't say Zetros say Secutor! The latest Mercedes agricultural monster mover on Biglorryblog! - Truckanddriver.co.uk]</ref>\n\n<gallery>\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros as a relief vehicle for the 2011 Tohoku Earthquake.jpg|Mercedes-Benz Zetros 1833 as a relief vehicle for the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros 1833 at IAA 2014.JPG|Zetros 1833 [[Recreational vehicle|RV]] at [[International Motor Show Germany|IAA 2014]]\nFile:60 Jahre Unimog - W\u00f6rth 2011 301 Entwicklungswerkstatt (5797108035).jpg|[[Rolling chassis]] of a Zetros 2733\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 R\u00fcstwagen.jpg|alt=Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 Heavy fire rescue truck|Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 [[Heavy rescue vehicle|technical rescue truck]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros GTF 6x6.JPG|Zetros 2733 of the [[German Army]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL.jpg|Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL platform of [[Lithuanian army]]\n</gallery>\n\n=== Technical characteristics ===\nOriginally introduced with a 7.2L diesel, a 12L variant was added in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com/en/trucks/zetros/powertrain|title=Powertrain|website=ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref>\n*Engine: 7,201 cc inline 6 cylinder diesel\n*Power: 326&nbsp;hp (240&nbsp;kW)\n*Torque: 1300Nm (958&nbsp;ft lbs)\n*Top speed: 55&nbsp;mph\n*Engine: 11,967 cc inline 6 cylinder diesel\n*Power: 428&nbsp;hp (315&nbsp;kW)\n*Torque: 2100Nm (1,549&nbsp;ft lbs)\n\n==Operators==\n[[File:Zetros operators.png|thumb|400px|Map with Zetros operators in blue]]\n\n===Current operators===\n*{{flag|Algeria}}\nAround 2 000 trucks are planned to be produced by the Algeria's National Company of Industrial Vehicles (SNVI) destined for the Algerian defence ministry.<ref>{{cite web|title=Algerian factory unveils new locally assembled truck for Algerian military|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38381|website=Defence Web|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20151009150440/http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38381|archivedate=9 October 2015|date=16 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Locally further developed into self-propelled artillery systems using the [[122 mm howitzer 2A18 (D-30)|D-30]] and [[T-12 antitank gun|T-12]] gun systems.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Binnie|first1=Jeremy|title=Algeria displays locally developed self-propelled artillery|url=http://www.janes.com/article/72018/|website=IHS Jane's 360|accessdate=6 July 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170706000423/http://www.janes.com/article/72018/algeria-displays-locally-developed-self-propelled-artillery|archivedate=6 July 2017|date=4 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Australia}}\nThe Zetros is used as a fertiliser spreader in the South East of South Australia.  It is a 4x4 version operated by Crossling Contractors based in [[Naracoorte,_South_Australia|Naracoorte]].\n\n*{{flag|Bulgaria}}\nThe [[Bulgarian Land Forces|Bulgarian army]] ordered the Zetros in 2009 to transport personnel and supplies.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.logistika.bg/adetails/2/1/85/95 |title=\u0410\u0440\u043c\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0441\u0434\u043e\u0431\u0438 \u0441 Zetros |journal=Bulgarian Transport Press |language=Bulgarian |accessdate=25 April 2012 |issue=4 |date=29 January 2009}}</ref> As of 2012, it operates 335 trucks with 30 more on order.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dikov|first1=Ivan|title=The Bulgaria 2011 Review: Defense|url=http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=135492|website=Novinite Sofia News Agency|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120911054452/http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=135492|archivedate=11 September 2012|location=Sofia|date=6 January 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Chile}}\nIn August 2016 Mercedes Benz has been awarded a contract to provide 330 trucks for the [[Chilean Army]]. The contract includes a batch of Zetros 2733 6x6 and [[Unimog]] U4000 4x4 vehicles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Porfilio|first1=Gabriel|title=Chile to purchase more than 300 Mercedes Benz trucks|url=http://www.janes.com/article/63282/|website=IHS Jane's 360|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170622153132/http://www.janes.com/article/63282/chile-to-purchase-more-than-300-mercedes-benz-trucks|archivedate=22 June 2017|location=Orlando|date=30 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Costa Rica}}\nThe first non military application of the Zetros 2733 was announced in June 2018 by the Costa Rican Firefighters as the organization acquired one. It will serve as transport for rescue crew and equipment in emergency situations as floods, hurricanes, storms, wild fires, volcanic eruptions and earthquakes.\n\n*{{flag|Germany}}\nThe [[German army]] has ordered a total of 110 armoured Zetros vehicles, 72 of which are supposed to serve in logistics units.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ralf |last=Wilke |date=25 November 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013 |publisher=[[Streitkr\u00e4ftebasis]] |language=German |title=Gesch\u00fctzter Transportraum |trans-title=Protected transportation space |url=http://www.streitkraeftebasis.de/portal/a/streitkraeftebasis/!ut/p/c4/NYvBCsIwEAX_aDepFdGbsRevImi9SJqGurVNwjZGED_e5OAbmMvw8IYZpxMNOpJ3esIrtoZ23RuWZ3cP9IHFciIDms2DElRCrmDUDi_l2Vsw3tlYHK2LlD2wjp4heI5TKS_mXIB6bIVslKjFf_K7rTcHdV7XVXNUJwzzvP8BsADx5A!!/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042633/http://www.streitkraeftebasis.de/portal/a/streitkraeftebasis/!ut/p/c4/NYvBCsIwEAX_aDepFdGbsRevImi9SJqGurVNwjZGED_e5OAbmMvw8IYZpxMNOpJ3esIrtoZ23RuWZ3cP9IHFciIDms2DElRCrmDUDi_l2Vsw3tlYHK2LlD2wjp4heI5TKS_mXIB6bIVslKjFf_K7rTcHdV7XVXNUJwzzvP8BsADx5A!!/ |archivedate=26 January 2013 }}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Lithuania}}\nUnknown quantity acquired in 2019. Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL platform for [[PzH 2000]] or [[Bergepanzer 2]] transportation<ref>[http://kariuomene.kam.lt/lt/naujienos_1887/lietuvos_kariuomeneje_bus_naudojami_dideles_galios_vilkikai.html]</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Mexico}}\n[[Mexican Army]] And [[Mexican Air Force]] have planned the purchase of 137 6x6 trucks, in three stages, beginning the first purchase of 46 in 2017\n\n*{{flag|Turkey}}\n[[Turkish Armed Forces]] use Zetros as [[HISAR (surface to air missile system)]] carrier.<ref>https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/turkey_could_deploy_local-made_air_defense_missile_systems_hisar-a_and_hisar-o_in_syria.html</ref>\n\n===Possible operators===\n*{{flag|Argentina}} \nIn 2016, Mercedes-Benz presents and exhibit the Zetros in the Directorate of Arsenals, the plant of the former TAMSE in Boulogne. As reported by the Defensa site, the Argentine Army is a former customer of Mercedes-Benz. The idea is that the Zetros can replace, in a gradual way, the current fleet of Unimog and MB 1114.<ref>https://autoblog.com.ar/2016/07/19/mercedes-benz-presento-el-zetros-en-el-ejercito-argentino/</ref>\n\n==Notable appearances in media==\nThe Zetros is one of 14 Mercedes-Benz vehicle models featured in the 2013 film ''[[A Good Day to Die Hard]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mercedes-Benz represented with 14 different models in the new film \"A Good Day to Die Hard\": G-Class, Sprinter, Unimog and Zetros save the World|url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656190-1-1568970-1-0-1-0-0-0-11701-614232-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html|work=Daimler|accessdate=14 July 2013}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nA 6x6 Zetros, called the Terrorbyte, is featured in the online mode of [[Grand Theft Auto V]].\n\nAlso appear in Ghost Recon Wildlands, simply called \"Military Truck\" and is used by [[UNIDAD]].\n\nThe Zetros also appears in the offroad racing game [[Asphalt Xtreme]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.special-trucks.eu/webspecial_mercedes-benz_zetros/en/ Zetros Web Special]\n*[http://www.missionrabies.com/thetruck/ Mercedes-Benz Zetros 6x6 Custom Build for [[Mission Rabies]] ]\n{{Mercedes-Benz}}\n\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz vehicles|Zetros]]\n[[Category:Mercedes-Benz trucks|Zetros]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Mercedes-Benz Zetros''' is an off-road truck for extreme operations. It was first presented at the 2008 [[Eurosatory]] defence industry trade show in Paris. The Zetros is manufactured at the [[Mercedes-Benz]] plant in [[W\u00f6rth am Rhein|W\u00f6rth]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cms.daimler.com/Projects/c2c/channel/documents/1828804_Daimler_Trucks_at_a_Glance_2012_en.pdf |title=Daimler Trucks at a Glance |year=2012 |page=25 |publisher=Daimler |accessdate=25 April 2012 }}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The truck is designed to be compatible with the [[Lockheed C-130 Hercules|Hercules C-130]] transport and also fits into a standard German railway carriage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.special-trucks.eu/webspecial_zetros/ |title=Transportable |work=The New Zetros |publisher=Mercedes Benz |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>\n[[File:Mercedes-Benz Zetros DSC01477.JPG|thumb|Zetros 2733 at the [[International Defence Industry Exhibition]] 2012]]\n\n== Variants ==\nThe Zetros is available with a choice of 326&nbsp;hp (240&nbsp;kW) or 428&nbsp;hp (315&nbsp;kW) engines<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com/en/trucks/zetros/powertrain|title=Powertrain|website=ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref> and all-wheel drive:\n* Zetros 1833 (4x4) \u2013 4,000 to 6,000&nbsp;kg payload\n* Zetros 2733 (6x6) \u2013 7,000 to 10,000&nbsp;kg payload\n\nAlthough normally used as a truck, the Zetros has also been put to work as an off-road tractor unit in the middle east.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mercedes' Middle Eastern Monster Mover\u2014the Zetros 6x6 gets down to work on Biglorryblog!|url=http://www.commercialmotor.com/big-lorry-blog/mercedes-middle-eastern-monster-mover--the-zetros-6x6-gets-down-to-work-on-biglorryblog#.UMvGNW9yGE0|work=Biglorryblog|accessdate=15 December 2012}}</ref> German company Harald Bruhn also introduced a Zetros-based agricultural trailer truck as the Secutor.<ref>[https://www.truckanddriver.co.uk/latest-stories/don-t-say-zetros-say-secutor-the-latest-mercedes-agricultural-monster-mover-on-biglorryblog/ Don't say Zetros say Secutor! The latest Mercedes agricultural monster mover on Biglorryblog! - Truckanddriver.co.uk]</ref>\n\n<gallery>\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros as a relief vehicle for the 2011 Tohoku Earthquake.jpg|Mercedes-Benz Zetros 1833 as a relief vehicle for the [[2011 T\u014dhoku earthquake and tsunami]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros 1833 at IAA 2014.JPG|Zetros 1833 [[Recreational vehicle|RV]] at [[International Motor Show Germany|IAA 2014]]\nFile:60 Jahre Unimog - W\u00f6rth 2011 301 Entwicklungswerkstatt (5797108035).jpg|[[Rolling chassis]] of a Zetros 2733\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 R\u00fcstwagen.jpg|alt=Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 Heavy fire rescue truck|Mercedes-Benz Zetros 2733 6x6 [[Heavy rescue vehicle|technical rescue truck]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz Zetros GTF 6x6.JPG|Zetros 2733 of the [[German Army]]\nFile:Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL.jpg|Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL platform of [[Lithuanian army]]\n</gallery>\n\n=== Technical characteristics ===\nOriginally introduced with a 7.2L diesel, a 12L variant was added in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com/en/trucks/zetros/powertrain|title=Powertrain|website=ksa.trucks.mercedesbenzmena.com|access-date=2017-11-19}}</ref>\n*Engine: 7,201 cc inline 6 cylinder diesel\n*Power: 326&nbsp;hp (240&nbsp;kW)\n*Torque: 1300Nm (958&nbsp;ft lbs)\n*Top speed: 55&nbsp;mph\n*Engine: 11,967 cc inline 6 cylinder diesel\n*Power: 428&nbsp;hp (315&nbsp;kW)\n*Torque: 2100Nm (1,549&nbsp;ft lbs)\n\n==Operators==\n[[File:Zetros operators.png|thumb|400px|Map with Zetros operators in blue]]\n\n===Current operators===\n*{{flag|Algeria}}\nAround 2 000 trucks are planned to be produced by the Algeria's National Company of Industrial Vehicles (SNVI) destined for the Algerian defence ministry.<ref>{{cite web|title=Algerian factory unveils new locally assembled truck for Algerian military|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38381|website=Defence Web|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20151009150440/http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38381|archivedate=9 October 2015|date=16 March 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> Locally further developed into self-propelled artillery systems using the [[122 mm howitzer 2A18 (D-30)|D-30]] and [[T-12 antitank gun|T-12]] gun systems.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Binnie|first1=Jeremy|title=Algeria displays locally developed self-propelled artillery|url=http://www.janes.com/article/72018/|website=IHS Jane's 360|accessdate=6 July 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170706000423/http://www.janes.com/article/72018/algeria-displays-locally-developed-self-propelled-artillery|archivedate=6 July 2017|date=4 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Australia}}\nThe zetros is used as a fertiliser spreader in the South East of South Australia.  It is a 4x4 version operated by Crossling Contractors based in Naracoorte.\n\n*{{flag|Bulgaria}}\nThe [[Bulgarian Land Forces|Bulgarian army]] ordered the Zetros in 2009 to transport personnel and supplies.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.logistika.bg/adetails/2/1/85/95 |title=\u0410\u0440\u043c\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0441\u0434\u043e\u0431\u0438 \u0441 Zetros |journal=Bulgarian Transport Press |language=Bulgarian |accessdate=25 April 2012 |issue=4 |date=29 January 2009}}</ref> As of 2012, it operates 335 trucks with 30 more on order.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dikov|first1=Ivan|title=The Bulgaria 2011 Review: Defense|url=http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=135492|website=Novinite Sofia News Agency|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120911054452/http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=135492|archivedate=11 September 2012|location=Sofia|date=6 January 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Chile}}\nIn August 2016 Mercedes Benz has been awarded a contract to provide 330 trucks for the [[Chilean Army]]. The contract includes a batch of Zetros 2733 6x6 and [[Unimog]] U4000 4x4 vehicles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Porfilio|first1=Gabriel|title=Chile to purchase more than 300 Mercedes Benz trucks|url=http://www.janes.com/article/63282/|website=IHS Jane's 360|accessdate=22 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20170622153132/http://www.janes.com/article/63282/chile-to-purchase-more-than-300-mercedes-benz-trucks|archivedate=22 June 2017|location=Orlando|date=30 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Costa Rica}}\nThe first non military application of the Zetros 2733 was announced in June 2018 by the Costa Rican Firefighters as the organization acquired one. It will serve as transport for rescue crew and equipment in emergency situations as floods, hurricanes, storms, wild fires, volcanic eruptions and earthquakes.\n\n*{{flag|Germany}}\nThe [[German army]] has ordered a total of 110 armoured Zetros vehicles, 72 of which are supposed to serve in logistics units.<ref>{{cite web |first=Ralf |last=Wilke |date=25 November 2013 |accessdate=18 December 2013 |publisher=[[Streitkr\u00e4ftebasis]] |language=German |title=Gesch\u00fctzter Transportraum |trans-title=Protected transportation space |url=http://www.streitkraeftebasis.de/portal/a/streitkraeftebasis/!ut/p/c4/NYvBCsIwEAX_aDepFdGbsRevImi9SJqGurVNwjZGED_e5OAbmMvw8IYZpxMNOpJ3esIrtoZ23RuWZ3cP9IHFciIDms2DElRCrmDUDi_l2Vsw3tlYHK2LlD2wjp4heI5TKS_mXIB6bIVslKjFf_K7rTcHdV7XVXNUJwzzvP8BsADx5A!!/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126042633/http://www.streitkraeftebasis.de/portal/a/streitkraeftebasis/!ut/p/c4/NYvBCsIwEAX_aDepFdGbsRevImi9SJqGurVNwjZGED_e5OAbmMvw8IYZpxMNOpJ3esIrtoZ23RuWZ3cP9IHFciIDms2DElRCrmDUDi_l2Vsw3tlYHK2LlD2wjp4heI5TKS_mXIB6bIVslKjFf_K7rTcHdV7XVXNUJwzzvP8BsADx5A!!/ |archivedate=26 January 2013 }}</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Lithuania}}\nUnknown quantity acquired in 2019. Mercedes-Benz ZETROS with Mercedes-Benz EMPL platform for [[PzH 2000]] or [[Bergepanzer 2]] transportation<ref>[http://kariuomene.kam.lt/lt/naujienos_1887/lietuvos_kariuomeneje_bus_naudojami_dideles_galios_vilkikai.html]</ref>\n\n*{{flag|Mexico}}\n[[Mexican Army]] And [[Mexican Air Force]] have planned the purchase of 137 6x6 trucks, in three stages, beginning the first purchase of 46 in 2017\n\n*{{flag|Turkey}}\n[[Turkish Armed Forces]] use Zetros as [[HISAR (surface to air missile system)]] carrier.<ref>https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/turkey_could_deploy_local-made_air_defense_missile_systems_hisar-a_and_hisar-o_in_syria.html</ref>\n\n===Possible operators===\n*{{flag|Argentina}} \nIn 2016, Mercedes-Benz presents and exhibit the Zetros in the Directorate of Arsenals, the plant of the former TAMSE in Boulogne. As reported by the Defensa site, the Argentine Army is a former customer of Mercedes-Benz. The idea is that the Zetros can replace, in a gradual way, the current fleet of Unimog and MB 1114.<ref>https://autoblog.com.ar/2016/07/19/mercedes-benz-presento-el-zetros-en-el-ejercito-argentino/</ref>\n\n==Notable appearances in media==\nThe Zetros is one of 14 Mercedes-Benz vehicle models featured in the 2013 film ''[[A Good Day to Die Hard]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mercedes-Benz represented with 14 different models in the new film \"A Good Day to Die Hard\": G-Class, Sprinter, Unimog and Zetros save the World|url=http://media.daimler.com/dcmedia/0-921-656190-1-1568970-1-0-1-0-0-0-11701-614232-0-1-0-0-0-0-0.html|work=Daimler